    Alle Klassen und Schnittstellen

    Klasse
    Beschreibung
    AdminCal
    The AdminCal class provides administrative functionalities for managing users, rooms, and floors within the application.
    AdminGUI
    The AdminGUI class represents the main frame for the Admin Dashboard.
    CustomKeyboard
    An implementation of a virtual keyboard using Swing.
    Direction
    The Direction enum represents the four cardinal directions: UP, RIGHT, DOWN, and LEFT.
    EmployeeGUI
    Represents the main graphical user interface (GUI) for the Employee/User level of the pathfinding application.
    FloorData
    The FloorData class manages the persistence and manipulation of floor information within the application.
    FloorData.Floor
    Represents a single floor entity with an ID and a lock status.
    GameState
    The GameState class represents the current state of the pathfinding or "Game" logic within the application.
    LoginCal
    The LoginCal class handles the core logic for user authentication by comparing the provided login credentials against user data stored in a file.
    LoginGUI
    The LoginGUI class provides the graphical user interface for user authentication (employee login).
    MapGUI
    The MapGUI class represents the main graphical user interface (GUI) for the pathfinding application.
    RoomData
    The RoomData class represents a single room entity and provides static methods for managing the persistent storage of all room data (CRUD operations) in a file.
    RouteCal
    The RouteCal class is a custom JPanel responsible for displaying the map, handling user interactions for route selection, rendering the pathfinding visualization, and executing the pathfinding logic (Breadth-First Search).
    UserData
    The UserData class represents a single user entity (username, password, role) and provides methods for managing the persistent storage of all user data (CRUD operations) in a file.
